		<div class="page-header">
						<h1>
															Adding an image or logo to your signature in Horde Mail									</h1>
			
																
				
					<div style='font-size:12px; color:#aaa; margin-bottom:-10px; padding-top:5px;'>
							<div style='float:left; margin-right:20px;'><span style='color:#606060;'>Written by </span><a href='https://plus.google.com/u/0/103891980085974966828/?rel=author'>Scott Mitchell</a></div>
							<div style='float:left; margin-right:20px;'><span style='color:#606060;'>Views:</span> <span name='page_views' id='page_views'>12,869</span></div>
							<div style='float:left; margin-right:20px;' title='Originally published: Jul 24, 2014'><span style='color:#606060;'>Published:</span> Nov 25, 2014</div>
							<div style='float:left; margin-right:20px;'><span style='color:#606060;'>Comments:</span> <a href='#comments'>46</a></div>
							<div style='clear:both;'></div>
						</div>
						</div>
		
	
		

	

								With the new upgrade to the Horde mail interface, you can now have images in your signature. For companies, the most common image to add is the company logo. Follow along with the instructions below as we demonstrate how to add your logo (or any other image) to your <a href="/support/email/horde-webmail/create-signature">email signature in Horde</a>.

<ol class="article_list">
  <li><a href="/support/email/horde-webmail/logging-into-horde">Log into your Horde mail interface</a>.<div style="clear:both;"></div></li>
  <li><a class="std_ss" href="//cdn.inmotionhosting.com/support/images/stories/edu/email/horde/add-signature-image/1-menu.png"><img   style="float:right; margin:0px 15px 15px 15px;" alt="" src="//cdn.inmotionhosting.com/support/images/stories/edu/email/horde/add-signature-image/1-menu.png" title="Click here to view the larger image" width="200" /></a>Once inside, hover over the cog image and then <strong>Preferences</strong>. Select <strong>Mail</strong> from the pop up menu.<div style="clear:both;"></div></li>
  <li><a class="std_ss" href="//cdn.inmotionhosting.com/support/images/stories/edu/email/horde/add-signature-image/2-click-personal-info.png"><img   style="float:right; margin:0px 15px 15px 15px;" alt="" src="//cdn.inmotionhosting.com/support/images/stories/edu/email/horde/add-signature-image/2-click-personal-info.png" title="Click here to view the larger image" width="200" /></a>Now click on the <strong>Personal Information</strong> link.<div style="clear:both;"></div></li>
  <li><a class="std_ss" href="//cdn.inmotionhosting.com/support/images/stories/edu/email/horde/add-signature-image/3-click-image-button.png"><img   style="float:right; margin:0px 15px 15px 15px;" alt="" src="//cdn.inmotionhosting.com/support/images/stories/edu/email/horde/add-signature-image/3-click-image-button.png" title="Click here to view the larger image" width="200" /></a>This page is where you set your signature. Scroll to the bottom area where the HTML editor is. This is the one with many different buttons. Find the <strong>image</strong> button and click it.<div style="clear:both;"></div></li>
  <li><a class="std_ss" href="//cdn.inmotionhosting.com/support/images/stories/edu/email/horde/add-signature-image/4-image-info.png"><img   style="float:right; margin:0px 15px 15px 15px;" alt="" src="//cdn.inmotionhosting.com/support/images/stories/edu/email/horde/add-signature-image/4-image-info.png" title="Click here to view the larger image" width="200" /></a>Enter the image link in the <strong>URL</strong> field. You are not able to upload the image directly to the server, so you will need to know the exact address of the image on your server. For example, this image is located at "<em>http://example.com/images/logo.png</em>". There are various optional fields here you can use to further customize the logo's size and/or its position.<div style="clear:both;"></div></li>
  <li><a class="std_ss" href="//cdn.inmotionhosting.com/support/images/stories/edu/email/horde/add-signature-image/5-add-link.png"><img   style="float:right; margin:0px 15px 15px 15px;" alt="" src="//cdn.inmotionhosting.com/support/images/stories/edu/email/horde/add-signature-image/5-add-link.png" title="Click here to view the larger image" width="200" /></a>After adjusting the options on the Image Info tab, it is a good idea to make the logo a link back to your website. Configure this tab for your logo to point to your website.<div style="clear:both;"></div></li>
</ol>
Below is a shot demonstrating the logo in a very simple test email. Note that you need to be sure to send the email in HTML format (by selecting a checkbox for HTML mail when composing) in order for the logo to be in the signature. If this is not done Horde will choose the <a href="/support/email/horde-webmail/create-signature">text-based signature if you have created one</a>.
<div style="clear:both;"></div><a class="std_ss" href="//cdn.inmotionhosting.com/support/images/stories/edu/email/horde/add-signature-image/after.png"><img   style="" alt="" src="//cdn.inmotionhosting.com/support/images/stories/edu/email/horde/add-signature-image/after.png" title="Click here to view the larger image" width="100%" /></a> 
	
						 </div>

	






